      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LEAP TO FAME (5) produced another 'off the canvas' style win in last week's qualifier when he worked, looked in danger but fought back in true warrior fashion. He is better known over further but that win was his seventh from nine mile attempts and he has recorded a win and a second in this race the last two years. There are plenty of challengers in a race packed with depth but there's no doubt he'll fight for it. CAPTAINS MISTRESS NZ (4) has been sensational in winning all six starts for Jason Grimson, two at Group 1 level including last week's Chariots of Fire. Has been tackling her own age or the mares so she faces a different level of pressure against the big guns but has brilliant speed and is five from five at the mile. SWAYZEE (2) gets the same draw he had when locked away in last year's Miracle Mile but he was terrific from the outside last week and looks right at his best again. THE JANITOR NZ (6) could be ready for the big time after sweeping home to win when first up last week.",
